---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 112
  - Title: II Convito
    Location: III vi 3
By: Dante
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Consummation of Desire
---
The desire for perfection ... is that desire which always makes every
pleasure appear incomplete, for there is no joy or pleasure so great in this
life that it can quench the thirst in our Soul.
